# ============================================================
# WORLD CORE POLICY
# ============================================================

status: canonical
layer: policy
domain: world
scope: world.core
system: civilization-os
owner: Boss
prepared_by: Zero

## purpose
Defines policy constraints for world.

## policy_rules
World policy constrains:
- which actions are world-scoped
- which cross-world actions are permitted
- what world detail may be disclosed
- when historical world data may be shown
- when world-bounded paths must be denied

## required_behavior
- world scope must be explicit
- disclosure scope must be explicit
- cross-world allowance must be explicit
- denial behavior must be explicit

## disclosure_matrix
- public world summary
- bounded world detail
- operator/reviewer detail
- historical reference detail
- denied output

## allowed_denied_matrix
- allow world-bounded action only for valid scope
- allow cross-world path only for explicit allowance
- allow historical reference only in valid mode
- deny hidden world-scope widening
- deny disclosure beyond allowed scope

## escalation_rules
If world identity,
world scope,
cross-world scope,
or disclosure scope is unclear,
the path must stop and escalate.

## review_checklist
- world scope policy is explicit
- disclosure matrix exists
- denial behavior is explicit
- escalation rules are explicit
